overview: The user tasked the agent with a comprehensive review and
  implementation of missing features for a sleep questionnaire application. The
  agent systematically addressed the identified gaps. Key implementations
  included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings,
  and the integration of detection logic and recommendations for complex sleep
  disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The agent also added a
  dedicated section for outbound links to external sleep and mental health
  resources. To enhance data analysis, weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness was implemented, and the CSV export functionality was significantly
  expanded to include all questionnaire responses. Finally, new questions were
  introduced to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue, with corresponding
  detection and guidance in the generated reports. All changes involved updating
  types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic.
